__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
.DS_Store

# Downloaded/generated datasets are large and reproducible from download.py + sampler.py + attack_generator.py — never commit
datasets/FUNSD/
datasets/CORD/
datasets/SROIE/
datasets/FigStep/
datasets/DocLayNet/

# sampled_images.json, doclaynet_sampled_images.json, and attack_metadata.json
# ARE committed (frozen, small, define the reproducible sample).
#
# datasets/attacks/ and datasets/doclaynet_attacks/ (the generated attacked
# images themselves) were committed for a while despite being generated
# output, specifically because attack_generator.py's font rendering is
# macOS-path-dependent - regenerating on another OS doesn't reproduce them
# byte-for-byte. Repo-cleanup decision (2026-07-20): un-tracked anyway, to
# keep the repo lightweight per standard ML-repo practice. Tradeoff this
# accepts: a fresh clone regenerates *visually equivalent* attacked images
# from the same committed attack_metadata.json + fixed seed, but not
# pixel-identical ones on a different machine/font set. Exact reproduction
# of previously reported numbers to the pixel is not guaranteed cross-
# machine as a result - re-running the pipeline is still fully functional.
datasets/attacks/
datasets/doclaynet_attacks/

typographic/outputs/
*.pkl
*.egg-info/

# Adversarial module: unlike Typographic, attack_generator.py here uses only
# procedural drawing (no system fonts), so patched images and candidate crops
# ARE perfectly reproducible cross-platform from committed code + committed
# clean images + fixed seed — no font-portability exception needed.
# adversarial/attack_metadata.json IS committed (frozen, small, defines the
# reproducible random choices), same reasoning as typographic's.
datasets/adversarial/attacks/
datasets/adversarial/candidates/
datasets/adversarial/candidate_labels.csv
datasets/adversarial/candidate_metadata.json
adversarial/outputs/

# Phase 5: same reasoning applies to the DocLayNet benchmark run -
# doclaynet_attack_metadata.json is committed (frozen, small, reproducible
# random choices); the generated images/crops/labels are not.
datasets/adversarial/doclaynet_attacks/
datasets/adversarial/doclaynet_candidates/
datasets/adversarial/doclaynet_candidate_labels.csv
datasets/adversarial/doclaynet_candidate_metadata.json
